      <h2>Pressure-fryer safety — PSI relief valve, door gasket, lid interlock</h2>
      <p>
        Commercial pressure fryers are genuinely dangerous equipment when safety-critical components fail. The
        pressure chamber operates at significant positive pressure during cook cycles, and the safety architecture
        that prevents over-pressurization, unsafe door opening, and chamber failure is not optional equipment —
        it's what keeps a pressure fryer from becoming a safety incident. Honest framing on this page: pressure-
        fryer safety service is scope our techs handle, not something operators should attempt DIY.
      </p>
      <p>
        The three safety-critical components we inspect and service on every Henny Penny pressure fryer call:
      </p>
      <ul class="check-list">
        <li><b>PSI relief valve</b> — the fail-safe that releases pressure if the primary pressure controls fail
          to maintain the safe operating range. Inspection every 90 days during routine service; manufacturer-
          recommended replacement cadence (typically annually for high-volume commercial use). Replacement and
          post-replacement pressure testing require specific training and the correct replacement parts; this is
          definitively not a DIY item.</li>
        <li><b>Door gasket and seal integrity</b> — the pressure chamber door gasket creates the sealed pressure
          environment during cook cycles. Gasket degradation leads to pressure loss (cook quality affected) and
          eventually to unsafe operation if the seal compromises under pressure. Inspection every service visit;
          replacement on condition or manufacturer-recommended cadence.</li>
        <li><b>Lid interlock mechanism</b> — the mechanical interlock that prevents the door from being opened
          while the chamber is under pressure. This is the last-line safety mechanism. Inspection and function
          verification on every service call. Failure of the interlock is a safety-critical condition that
          requires immediate repair before the fryer is returned to service.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The authorized-service path for Henny Penny pressure fryers routes through trained providers specifically
        because of these safety requirements. Our techs have pressure-fryer service training, carry the correct
        replacement parts, and perform post-service verification testing. We document the PSI relief valve
        inspection and service values, gasket condition, and lid interlock function in every Henny Penny work
        order.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

